-- LeBron James Overcomes Flu-Like Symptoms to Score 31 as Heat Defeat Lakers
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-20T05:30:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/lebron-james-overcomes-flu-like-symptoms-to-7score-31-as-heat-defeat-laker.html
LeBron James  scored 31 points after
being sent home during practice with flu-like symptoms to lead
the Miami Heat to a 98-87 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers.  Two nights earlier, James tallied 33 points as the Heat
rallied to beat the San Antonio Spurs 120-98.  Last night, Chris Bosh scored 15 points for the Heat (10-4),
who held a 52-37 halftime advantage at AmericanAirlines Arena in
Miami, where they own a 5-1 record.  Pau Gasol had 26 points and Kobe Bryant added 24 for the
Lakers (10-6), who are 1-5 on the road.  Miami was without  Dwyane Wade , who has a sprained right
ankle, for the second straight National Basketball Association
game.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
